'''Mehmet Tahsini''' (1864-?) was an [[Albanians|Albanian]] politician, active in the [[Ottoman Empire]] and [[Albania]].

He was born in 1864 in [[Gjirokastër]] and started his career as a professor of History in [[Edirne]]. After 1895 he served as [[kaymakam]] in [[Eastern Anatolia]].<ref name="Özdalga">{{cite book|last=Özdalga|first=Elisabeth |title=Late Ottoman society: the intellectual legacy|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sRtTyyGIgXsC&pg=PA311&dq=mehmed+tahsin&cd=3#v=onepage&q=mehmed%20tahsin&f=false|accessdate=2010-08-14|date=March 2005|publisher=Taylor & Francis, Inc.|isbn=0-415-34164-7|pages=311}}</ref>

